Cauliflower Alfredo Sauce with Zucchini Noodles

2 c cauliflower, chopped into small florets
½ tbsp extra-virgin olive oil
1 shallot, peeled and minced
1 garlic clove, peeled and minced
½ c unsweetened organic almond milk
¼ c nutritional yeast
juice of ½ lemon
½ tsp sea salt
4 c cooked zucchini noodles

In a large pot of boiling water, cook the cauliflower in a steamer until tender, about 6 min. In a small saute pan, warm the olive oil over moderate heat. Add the shallot and garlic and cook for 3 min or until softened. In a blender, add the cooked cauliflower, shallots and garlic, almond milk, nutritional yeast, lemon, and sea salt and process until thoroughly blended, about 30 s. Serve with the cooked zucchini noodles.

